com.acrolinx.javasdk.api.extraction

Interface CheckInformationBuilder<DocumentType extends Document>

  • Type Parameters:
    DocumentType - The type of the Document one of AcrolinxFactory.documents() or your own type inheriting from Document or using AbstractDocument.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CheckInformationBuilderImpl

    public interface CheckInformationBuilder<DocumentType extends Document>
    The CheckInformationBuilder is used to create CheckInformation.

      • withAbsoluteDocumentOffset

        CheckInformationBuilder<DocumentType> withAbsoluteDocumentOffset(int absoluteDocumentOffset)
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        The CheckInformationBuilder for chaining.
        Note: in BlockDocuments the mapping is done via: DocumentPartMapping.getOriginalDocumentParts(com.acrolinx.javasdk.api.extraction.documents.block.Range) .

      • withCheckScope

        CheckInformationBuilder<DocumentType> withCheckScope(CheckScope checkScope)

        The CheckInformationBuilder for chaining.

      • withCompleteCheck

        CheckInformationBuilder<DocumentType> withCompleteCheck(boolean isCompleteCheck)
        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • withServerSideXmlExtraction

        CheckInformationBuilder<DocumentType> withServerSideXmlExtraction(boolean isUseServerSideXmlExtraction)
        Set to XML to use server-side XML extraction. Requires that the language server is configured to support server-side XML extraction. Also the FileFormat of the Document should match.
        Parameters:
        isUseServerSideXmlExtraction - whether the server should expect an XML document and do XML extraction on the server-side
        Returns:
        an instance of the same CheckSettingsBuilder to allow chaining
